data.text: People hating on this tweet and I'm just over here like https://t.co/5GMZP8FcFh

@MitzyRosencrant The fact that regardless of anything, this is a trans issue to me. The reason I reported it was specifically because it was transphobic. While yes all hate speech should be reported I was focusing on the fact that it was towards trans people as that is an important matter with me

@MitzyRosencrant Hate speech regarding a community of people's human rights is a tad different than hate speech towards one political figure that is the leader of our country. But yes you might be able to put it in the same category if you stand far away and squint at it

@MitzyRosencrant Either way you're making broad assumptions about topics that don't have to do with trans issues. What connection are you drawing that makes it so that me reporting transphobic hate speech automatically means that I wouldn't report something about Trump?
@MitzyRosencrant That is literally a completely different issue and totally unrelated to how people treat transgender people
@LAX_Lady17 You should report Instagram. Reach for the stars
The memes page has since taken it down on there own but just the fact that Instagram doesn't see that as being transphobic and offensive blows my mind
